{{Beauty pageant | winner = [[Marilyn Meseke]] | represented = {{flagicon|Ohio}} [[Miss Ohio]] | date = September 10, 1938 | presenters = | entrants = 44 | placements = 15 | venue = [[Steel Pier]], [[Atlantic City]], [[New Jersey]] | broadcaster = }}'''Miss America 1938''', the 12th [[Miss America]] pageant, was held at the [[Steel Pier]] in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]] on September 10, 1938.<ref>{{cite news|title='Beautiful But Dumb' Legend Haunts Miss America 1938|date=1938-09-12|publisher=Chester Times|page=7}}</ref> The selection by the 15 judges of [[Miss Ohio]] over [[Miss California]] surprised the audience attending the event. Famous [[Broadway theater|Broadway]] producer [[Earl Carroll]], ''[[Murder at the Vanities]]'', also disagreed with their choice and took the [[runner-up]] to [[New York]] where he performed a coronation of [[Miss California]] as "the true Miss America" shortly after the official pageant. Carroll's actions resulted in widespread publicity of the incident.<ref>{{cite news|title=Producer Carroll Differs in Choice of Miss America |last=Associated Press|date=1938-09-12|publisher=Oshkosh Daily Northwestern|page=5}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meet Miss America - Both of 'Em|last=Associated Press Wire Photo|date=1938-09-12|publisher=Oakland Tribune|page=5}}</ref>
